Image diagnosis: nuclear medicine. Delineation of malignant tumor by scintigraphy is divided into two categories visualizing tumor as positive foci or negative foci. Our clinical experiences with 67Ga, 201Tl, 131I-MIBG and 131Imonoclonal antibodies including 111In-ZMEO18 were described and literatures relevant to positive delineation of malignant tumor were reviewed.